  "text": "Culture of immortalized neonatal rat cardiomyocytes (H10 cells) and generation of stably transfected cell clones (NDPKϩ cells) has been described. [CITATION_1] Neonatal rat cardiomyocytes (NRCM) were isolated as described [CITATION_2] and were infected with the indicated multiplicity of infection (MOI) under serum-free conditions 48 hours after plating and subsequently cultured supplemented with 2% FCS for 48 hours. Adult rat cardiomyocytes (ARCM) were isolated from Sprague-Dawley rats using a collagenase digestion method [CITATION_3] and were infected 1 hour after plating and further cultured for 48 hours in a HEPES-modified medium 199 (M199, Sigma S7528, supplemented with 5 mmol/L taurine, 5 mmol/L carnitine, 5 mmol/L creatine, 5 mmol/L N-mercaptoproprionyl glycine, 0.1 mol/L insulin, 10,000 U/mL penicillin and 10 mg/mL streptomycin, pH 7.25).",
